All three changes have been applied correctly. Here is a summary of what was changed in `/Users/4thwithme/Documents/repo/recommendations-service/src/unit-tests/mms.service.unit-spec.ts`:

**Line 337** — Simple call assertion updated to use the new object signature:
```typescript
// before
expect(errorSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(generalError);
// after
expect(errorSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith({ err: generalError });
```

**Lines 352-355** — Extracting the error from the first call argument now dereferences `.err` from the object:
```typescript
// before
const serviceErrorArg = serviceCallArgs?.[0] as Error;
// after
const serviceErrorArg = (serviceCallArgs?.[0] as { err: Error }).err;
```

**Lines 357-361** — The decorator call previously spread across two positional args (`[0]` for message, `[1]` for context object) is now a single object argument with `err` and `context` properties:
```typescript
// before
const decoratorMessage = decoratorCallArgs[0] as string;
expect(decoratorMessage).toContain('failed');
const decoratorContext = decoratorCallArgs[1]!;
expect(decoratorContext['errorMessage']).toBe('This is a string error');
// after
const decoratorArg = decoratorCallArgs[0] as { err: Error; context?: Record<string, unknown> };
expect(decoratorArg.err.message).toContain('failed');
expect(decoratorArg.context?.['errorMessage']).toBe('This is a string error');
```
